Method behavioural requirements:
- The integer 2D array parameter `grid` must not be null.
- The integer 2D array parameter `hits` must not be null.
- The integer result array length is equal to the length of the integer 2D array parameter `hits`.
- For each element in the integer 2D array parameter `hits`, if the brick at that location is erased, the number of bricks that will fall after the erasure is applied must be calculated and stored in the corresponding index of the integer result array.